## Important Platform Truths You Must Account For

Your markdown must be grounded in these realities:

- DRAMAC is multi-tenant.
- The hierarchy is platform -> agency -> client -> site -> portal user/team.
- The client portal is white-labeled and should reflect agency/site branding.
- The client portal is module-aware and permission-aware.
- Portal access is gated by client-level permissions plus site-level overrides.
- Live chat, booking, ecommerce, CRM, automation, invoicing, marketing, domains/email, blog, media, SEO, and support all matter to the portal experience.
- Live chat is not just a messaging UI. It is connected to booking, orders, quotes, payment guidance, AI assistance, agent routing, and customer context.
- Booking and ecommerce flows create or update chat conversations and also rely on notifications and automation.
- The notification architecture is event-driven. Do not assume a direct hardcoded notification path is the only truth.
- Transactional email reliability matters platform-wide, not only inside one module.
- Nothing in the portal should depend on hardcoded niche-specific content.
- The portal must be genuinely mobile-first and production-grade, not simply desktop pages squeezed onto smaller screens.

